definitions.definition: Of, relating to, or consisting of matter , especially physical .
examples: This compound has a number of interesting material properties.

definitions.definition: Of, relating to, or affecting physical well-being ; corporeal ; bodily .
( logic ) Of or relating to the matter of reasoning , as distinguished from the form of it, especially empirical .
( especially law ) Having real importance or great consequences ; significant ; substantial .
examples: found a material difference between two things
You've made several material contributions to this project.
This is the most material fact in this lawsuit.

definitions.definition: Relating to or concerned with what is purely physical rather than intellectual or spiritual , especially excessively so; materialistic .
examples: Don't let material concerns get in the way of living a happy life.

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) Full of substance or otherwise meaning .
